# Internationalization (next-intl)

The app uses **[next-intl](https://next-intl.dev/)** for UI strings and locale-aware formatting. Prefer **no path-prefix locales** (`/en/...`).

## Locale resolution

- **`getRequestConfig`** (`src/i18n/request.ts`): on **every request**, resolve `locale` — **if a Clerk user is present**, use **only Clerk** (`clerkClient.users.getUser`, reading **`unsafeMetadata.language`** normalized to supported slugs). **If signed out**, use **only** a validated **`locale` cookie** (or default `en`). **Never** use the cookie for locale when the user is signed in.
- **Signed-in users**: read/write preferred language via **Clerk user metadata** (saved from `src/components/settings-page.tsx` through a **Server Action** that validates allowed locales with **Zod**, then updates the user via the **Clerk server SDK** — never trust client-supplied user ids).
- **Signed-out users**: **`locale` cookie** is the only guest mechanism for remembering language choice (still validate against supported locales when reading and writing).

## Stack

- **`messages/{locale}.json`** — nested message trees; ICU message syntax for plurals, rich text, and variables.
- **`src/i18n/request.ts`** — `getRequestConfig`: implement the branch above, validate against supported locales, `import()` the matching JSON, return `{ locale, messages, ... }`.
- **`next.config.ts`** — `createNextIntlPlugin` pointing at `./src/i18n/request.ts` (or this repo’s path).
- **Root `src/app/layout.tsx`** — `NextIntlClientProvider` with **`locale` + `messages`** from the server so the tree matches what `getRequestConfig` resolved for that request.

## Usage

```tsx
// ✅ Async Server Component
import { getTranslations } from "next-intl/server";
const t = await getTranslations("HomePage");

// ✅ Client Component
"use client";
import { useTranslations } from "next-intl";
const t = useTranslations("HomePage");
```

- Use **`getLocale()`** / **`useLocale()`** for dates, numbers, lists, and RTL-aware layout.
- Avoid raw user-facing strings; keys live in **`messages/*.json`**.

## Changing language (settings)

- **Signed in**: **Server Action** updates **Clerk metadata** only (Zod-validated locale slugs); then **`router.refresh()`** so the next request re-reads Clerk.
- **Signed out**: set or clear the **`locale` cookie** only (Zod-validated, Server Action or equivalent); **do not** write guest locale to Clerk. Refresh so `getRequestConfig` picks up the cookie.

## Anti-patterns

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — hardcoded UI copy
<h1>My Decks</h1>

// ❌ BAD — using the `locale` cookie for locale when a Clerk user is signed in

// ✅ GOOD — messages + t()
<h1>{t("title")}</h1>
```

Do **not** introduce a second i18n stack; extend **`messages/`** and next-intl APIs only.
